The paper discusses the use of virtual currencies and time-locked puzzles to incentivize forwarding nodes in a multihop communication network. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and network security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses congestion control techniques, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses latency-sensitive applications such as video streaming and augmented reality, which fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
